Source: UN Integrated Regional Information Networks (UIRIN, News, Wed 18
May 2005 [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/printable/200505180752.html>

South Africa: Government Declines to Comment On New AIDS Report
-------------------------------------------------
The South African health department has declined to comment on a startling
new HIV/AIDS report, arguing that the document has not yet been
"officially" released.
According to the Medical Research Council report on cause-specific death
rates for each of the country's 9 provinces, AIDS was the number-one cause
of death, except in the Western Cape, which has the lowest HIV prevalence
figures. Health department spokesman Solly Mabotha was quoted by the South
African Press Association as saying: "The report has not been released
officially, which means the minister and the director-general haven't seen
it yet. We therefore cannot comment."
The findings in the report, which is already available to news agencies on
request, showed that almost 30 percent of deaths in 2000 were caused by
HIV/AIDS.
[This above report does not necessarily reflect the views of the United
Nations].
